1.  Launch your environment
2. Install JDK
3. Navigate to the root directory for your service (every service must be in its own directory)
4. Bootstrap your microservice with Gradle or Maven by contacting spring.io (you can use curl or you can go to the website directly).  In the end, you need the starter code.
5. Delete the demo test file
6.  delete the demo directory and main class
7.  Create the Main Application (mostly copy and paste code)
8.  Craft the controller (define all of your end points and your methods)
9.  Build the Application with Gradle or Maven (compile, grab all dependencies, create a jar file out of everything).
10.  Run the application
11.  Optionally, you can put this service into a Docker Container (but this often happens with your devops team or whoever controls Jenkins
